He responded, “Events, my dear boy, events.”Unfortunately, we cannot know what the events of the next four years will be.
We cannot select the president who will best fit the events if we do not know which events will be happening.
Which candidate has the best potential to grow into a good president, giving the events that we do not know are coming?
We have to wonder which presidential candidate is most immune from the seduction of power.
Which candidate will best handle his own demons, and which will best handle “events, my dear boy, events?”Swickard is a weekly columnist for this site.